stand_up_comedy.title: Stand Up Comedy
stand_up_comedy.description: Featuring live specials from some of today's sharpest comedic minds, we're bringing the comedy club to you.

255765.title: Jeffrey Ross No Offense: Live From New Jersey
255765.description: Respected and feared, comedian Jeffrey Ross decided to take his hilarious and heartfelt brand of insult humor on the road.

257296.title: Paul Mooney: Analyzing White America
257296.description: In this unabashedly blunt stand-up special, comedian Paul Mooney turns his focus toward racism and White America with fearless insight and humor.

279390.title: Comic Relief: The Greatest
279390.description: This collection plays host to the best 20 years of Comic Relief. Join Billy, Whoopi, Robin and the rest of the greatest comedians on Earth as they throw their best stuff at a national disaster.

302493.title: Shaquille O'Neal Presents: All Star Comedy Jam - South Beach
302493.description: The all-star comedy line-up includes host D.L. Hughley and featured comics Earthquake, Lavell Crawford, Melanie Comarcho, and Arnez J.

302494.title: Shaquille O'Neal Presents: All Star Comedy Jam - Live From Dallas
302494.description: Comedian Mo'nique hosts Shaq's All Star Comedy Jam in Dallas, Texas featuring Paul Mooney, Corey Holcomb, George Willborn and Michael Blackson.

302495.title: Shaquille O'Neal Presents: All Star Comedy Jam - Live From Las Vegas
302495.description: Shaquille O'Neal presents some of stand-up's freshest talent, as they bring down the house in this high-energy night of comedy!

304766.title: Shaquille O'Neal Presents: All Star Comedy Jam - Atlanta
304766.description: Shaquille O'Neal presents today's most hilarious stand-up comedians LIVE from Atlanta.

304767.title: Shaquille O'Neal Presents: All Star Comedy Jam - Orlando
304767.description: Funnyman Gary Owen hosts stand-up comedy's most talented and sought after comedians; Capone, Lil' Duval, Tony Roberts and Jay Pharoah.

305391.title: Shaq & Cedric the Entertainer Present: All Star Comedy Jam
305391.description: Cedric the Entertainer is back as he hosts the All Star Comedy Jam, handpicking some of the industry's most talented and sought after comedians.

313906.title: Mike Epps Presents: Live from Club Nokia
313906.description: The jokes are funnier than ever in this hilarious new comedy special that showcases Epps, in addition to a variety of talented comedians.

318227.title: Cheech & Chong: Puff Puff Laugh
318227.description: Cheech & Chong host a hazy night full of stoner comedy at Just for Laughs in Montreal, the largest international comedy festival in the world.

318228.title: Night Of A Million Opinions
318228.description: Lewis Black, the Angriest Man in America, hosts a roster of opinionated comics at the Just For Laughs Festival.

327645.title: Totally Bill Hicks
327645.description: This special consists of two parts: “It's Just A Ride”, a documentary about Hicks' life which features interviews from friends, admirers, and family; “Revelations”, a recording of his last live performance in the United Kingdom.

327698.title: Gina Yashere: Skinny Bitch
327698.description: Witty, razor-sharp observations abound in this stand-up performance from Gina Yashere. From bits about her mom and men, to colonic irrigation and luggage this special leaves no stone unturned.

327705.title: Jeff Garcia: Low Budget Madness
327705.description: Shot live at San Manuel Indian Bingo and Casino in Highland, CA, Jeff Garcia's Low Budget Madness is packed with hilarious sketches that will leave you in stitches and remind you why audiences all over the world can't get a enough of Jeff Garcia!

327719.title: Morgan Murphy: Irish Goodbye
327719.description: Morgan Murphy brings dry and self-deprecating wit to the stage for this hilarious, gin-soaked special. Murphy's first target is always herself, but won't hesitate to bring down everyone from Planned Parenthood to teenage sexters.

365900.title: Arnez J.: Racially Motivated
365900.description: Tackling everything from race relations to family life to hilarious impersonations, Arnez J is laugh-out-loud funny in his one-hour special.

365901.title: Craig Ferguson: I'm Here to Help
365901.description: Craig Ferguson unleashes his trademark stream-of-consciousness comedy before a sold-out crowd, riffing on fatherhood, Helen of Troy and shark penises. His show's not safe for kids -- or the easily offended!

365909.title: Jim Breuer: And Laughter For All
365909.description: Marriage and parenthood won't keep die-hard metalhead comedian Jim Breuer from losing his manic sense of humor in this hilarious live show.

365910.title: Josh Blue: Delete
365910.description: With an undeniably unique world view, Blue explores preconceived notions of disability and how the community feels about being called “inspirational.”

365911.title: Matt Braunger: Big Dumb Animal
365911.description: Recorded live at The Bell House in Brooklyn, Big Dumb Animal is Matt Braunger at his best. He gives everyone a glimpse at what it's like to be a big dumb animal with an anger problem. He explores a vast array of topics ranging from the absurdity of a quiet Jägerbomb to his overly nice hometown of Portland, Oregon.

365924.title: Tom Papa: Freaked Out
365924.description: Famously upbeat comedian Tom Papa delivers a stand-up performance that includes his observations on the perils of raising daughters, and more. Executive produced by Rob Zombie.

401152.title: Tom Segura: Completely Normal
401152.description: Radio, television and live performance veteran Tom Segura shares a few off-hand appraisals on hotels and hobbies with a cool and thoughtful demeanor.

401158.title: Sinbad: Where U Been
401158.description: Sinbad hits the stage hard as he speaks truth to the burning subjects of the day, from poverty and politics to where he's been keeping himself.

401159.title: Sinbad: Make Me Wanna Holla
401159.description: A stand-up special covering the everything from the life advice his parents gave him to people with no talent having clothing lines and more.

401165.title: Kims of Comedy
401165.description: The Original Kims break new ground with an uncompromising look at Asian culture and some hilarious ethnic hang-ups. Featured are 4 of the top Asian comedians on stage today: Bobby Lee, Kevin Shea, Steve Byrne, and Dr. Ken Jeong.

440278.title: Eddie Griffin: You Can Tell 'Em I Said It
440278.description: The excitable comic again proves why he is one of the world’s premiere funnymen, ripping into racial stereotypes, Viagra, the First Lady, and more.

440466.title: Kevin Hart Presents: Lil Rel Howery - RELevent
440466.description: Hart hosts the high-energy comic who riffs on his upbringing, raising kids, and public transportation, proving he can be hilarious and relevant.

455842.title: Jim Norton: Contextually Inadequate
455842.description: The notoriously filthy comedian blends his usual self-loathing hilarity with a biting look at current events in this uproarious stand-up special.

455907.title: Ben Bailey: Live and Uncensored
455907.description: The Emmy-winning comic shines in a no-holds-barred performance that highlights his sharp writing, inspired improv, wit, and infectious energy.

461206.title: Kevin Hart Presents: Plastic Cup Boys
461206.description: Filmed live and led by Kevin Hart, the comedy group The Plastic Cup Boyz step into the spotlight with their hilarious stand-up and sketches.

463166.title: Andrew Santino: Homefield Advantage
463166.description: The comedian Andrew Santino goes home to Chicago for a comedy special, riffing on topics like bachelorette parties, severe acne, and his childhood.

463168.title: Kathleen Madigan: Madigan Again
463168.description: Her Irish Catholic Midwest family, pills in her mom’s purse, touring Afghanistan, an unparalleled love of John Denver…are all fodder for this special.

463172.title: Joey Coco Diaz: Sociably Unacceptable
463172.description: ItÍs been 25 years in the making and now...ÍUncle Joey DiazÍ is at Seeso for his 1st MOTHERFUCKING SPECIAL...Sociably Unacceptable. Prepare yourselves savages.

467476.title: Comedy After Dark
467476.description: Exotic dancers, porn stars and late-night comedy veterans mix it up in these deliriously dirty stand-up sets for the after-hours crowd.

467488.title: Gary Owen : Upgraded
467488.description: This special features a live performance by the funnyman, sharing his angry rants and witty observations, and a documentary on the making of the show.

477589.title: Christopher Titus: Amerigeddon
477589.description: Stand-up comedian Christopher Titus delivers the laughs in his take on the world since Trump and tries to unite the audience through sharp humor.

477920.title: Cheech Marin & Friends: Live From South Beach
477920.description: Cheech Marin, America’s favorite stoner and legend of Latino comedy, hosts a non-stop, stand-up laugh-fest with five Latino comics on the rise.

478059.title: Ian Bagg: Conversations
478059.description: The Canadian comedian, shares his sharp, biting wit on topics such as immigration, transgender bathrooms, and women's obsession with yoga pants.

478061.title: Bryan Callen: Never Grow Up
478061.description: The comedian examines the way our modern culture works, and wonders why we feel the need to view each other in such a narrow box.

478064.title: Brian Posehn: 25x2
478064.description: The comedian discovers a renewed passion for a sci-fi franchise, discusses the loss of his heroes, and his hot takes on certain recording artists.

478074.title: Steve-O: Guilty as Charged
478074.description: From his humble beginnings as a circus clown to becoming a star of the monster hit Jackass, comedian and author Steve-O has done it all—and then some.

478088.title: Willie Barcena: The Truth Hurts
478088.description: Stand-up comic Willie Barcena’s hilarious special, filmed in El Paso, bluntly questions everything from religion and dating to ladies with big feet.

480342.title: Jim Norton: American Degenerate
480342.description: Jim Norton’s second premium stand-up show, hilariously dishing on a wide range of topics that usually lead back to sex.

486668.title: Ron White: A Little Unprofessional
486668.description: With cigar and scotch in hand, the comedian delivers over an hour of new material in this live performance at the Paramount Theater in Austin, TX.

486952.title: Ladies on Laughter
486952.description: Six women of color try to make it as stand-up comedians in North Carolina while facing discrimination from promoters, male comedians, and society.

487597.title: Chonda Pierce: Girl Talk
487597.description: The preacher’s daughter and clean comedian shares personal and hilarious stories about living life through a Southern perspective.

488355.title: Mo'Nique: One Night Stand
488355.description: The multi-talented Oscar winner takes her unique voice and side-splitting act to the stage, in this hilarious stand-up comedy special.

489716.title: Sheryl Underwood: Too Much Information
489716.description: The outrageously honest comedian brings her side-splitting observations about life to the Dallas stage in this hilarious stand-up special.

489891.title: Dan Cummins: Don't Wake the Bear
489891.description: When the stand-up comic mixes his odd observational humor with serious subjects, like child rearing, or gun control, the results are hilarious.

489896.title: Margaret Cho: PsyCHO
489896.description: The iconic satirical comedian discusses everything from harams to female empowerment. It’s equal parts provocative, hilarious, and thought-provoking.

489898.title: Jeff Dunham: Very Special Christmas Special
489898.description: The multi-platinum selling comedian invites his puppet friends, including Walter, Peanut, and Bubba J, to join him on his first holiday special.

489901.title: Jeff Dunham: Minding the Monsters
489901.description: The comedian and ventriloquist extraordinaire, along with this felt friends, visits a haunted house where hilarious chaos ensues.

489902.title: Jeff Dunham: Arguing With Myself
489902.description: Join Jeff and his outspoken felt pals: Walter, Peanut, José Jalapeño, Bubba J, and Sweet Daddy Dee for an evening of laughs and observations.

489959.title: Sam Kinison: Breaking the Rules
489959.description: The late, great comic once dubbed “the cuddly anti-Christ” knows no limits, as he riffs on the importance of lies in marriage, necrophilia, and more.

490027.title: Todd Barry: Crowd Work Tour
490027.description: Without any prepared material, the comedian solely uses crowd-generated bits, to hilarious results. Watch as he riffs, banters, and wows.

495323.title: Rita Rudner: A Tale of Two Dresses
495323.description: The famed Vegas headliner returns, as witty, insightful,and cutting as ever, as she riffs on life as a sixty-something in today's America.

495334.title: Doug Stanhope: Beer Hall Putsch
495334.description: Named after Hitler’s first failed coup attempt, the comic’s stand-up special draws you deeper into his twisted, hilarious, yet compassionate mind.

495346.title: Steve Lemme & Kevin Heffernan: The Potential Farewell Tour
495346.description: This filmmaking and stand-up comedy duo ‘potentially’ appear for the very last time together on stage for a night of laughs, jokes and beers.

495406.title: Dennis Miller: Fake News, Real Jokes
495406.description: The king of dry wit is back to take down the current political and social climate — from selfies to airline travel to Donald Trump and the media.

495605.title: Adam Ferrara: Funny as Hell
495605.description: The stand-up comic and character actor muses on his wacky family dynamics, messed up romantic relationships, and other topics with honesty and wit.

499791.title: George Carlin: It's Bad for Ya
499791.description: The final HBO special from this comic legend challenges the audience on the failed state of American culture with his signature hilarious insight.

499812.title: George Carlin: Life Is Worth Losing
499812.description: In his 13th stand-up special, Carlin crosses boundaries and invades comfort zones with some of the most darkly hilarious material of his career.

501449.title: George Wallace: The Vegas Bootleg
501449.description: Comedian George Wallace’s live finale of his 10-year residency at the Flamingo Hotel, featuring musings on power, dating and hilarious revelations.

501493.title: Keedar Whittle: Hear Me Out
501493.description: Keedar Whittle’s outrageous set addressing the ways boyfriends can still be creeps, why exes should stay that way, and the bonds of nutty families.

503291.title: George Carlin: On Campus
503291.description: The revered stand-up comic discusses his New York City school days, as well as other memorable bits, including: “The Prayer” and “Consumer Hints.”

503292.title: George Carlin: George's Best Stuff
503292.description: The legendary stand-up performs his best bits, including: A Place For My Stuff,” “Dogs and Cats,” and “Seven Words You Can Never Say on Television.”

503293.title: George Carlin: Doin' It Again
503293.description: The iconic stand-up comedian is fearless when it comes to highlighting mankind’s worst traits, as he does in this special, filmed in New Jersey.

503294.title: George Carlin: Jammin' in New York
503294.description: Watch the legendary stand-up’s award-winning and personal favorite special, shot in his hometown, NYC. He discusses the “Little Things We Share.”

503295.title: George Carlin: Back in Town
503295.description: The legendary comic’s ninth HBO stand-up special includes his unique observations on topics like: abortion, capital punishment, and bodily functions.

504450.title: George Carlin: Complaints & Grievances
504450.description: The 12th HBO special of the veteran comic that tackled everything from 9/11 to the Ten Commandments. Recorded live at the Beacon Theater in New York.

504456.title: George Carlin: You Are All Diseased
504456.description: The famed counterculture comic returns to New York’s Beacon Theater to rant about religion, family, airport security, advertising and much more.

504457.title: George Carlin at USC
504457.description: In this standup special at the University of Southern California, the indignant comic exposes society’s hypocrisies in bits like “Old Folks & Kids.”

504531.title: Steve Treviño: 'Til Death
504531.description: This hilarious comedy special includes Treviño’s take on living in Texas, as well as the daily joys and struggles of balancing marriage and kids.

504533.title: Jill-Michele Meleán: White / Latina
504533.description: The half-Bolivian, half-Irish comic talks about navigating vastly different cultural identities while creating her own brand of funny.

504547.title: Bryan Callen: Complicated Apes
504547.description: In his third special, Callen examines why we feel the need to label every part of our identity, and how to survive the world without going nuts.

504549.title: Barry Brewer: Chicago, I'm Home
504549.description: With over 15 years as a stand-up, Barry Brewer has a lot to say to his sold out crowd at the Studebaker Theater, where he recounts his life.

504563.title: Jim Gaffigan: Noble Ape
504563.description: The stand-up comedy star describes how his wife faced a medical crisis, and he attempted to hold down the fort for their five children.

504601.title: George Carlin: Live at Carnegie
504601.description: The brainy comedian ignites the stage at NYC’s iconic Carnegie Hall, with his unique perceptions, outrageous physical humor, and brilliant mimicry.

505057.title: TK Kirkland: Are There Any Questions?
505057.description: Get ready for the underground stand-up superstar’s seminar-like set, which features truths on relationships, sex, and self-esteem.

505070.title: I Ain't Scared of You: A Tribute to Bernie Mac
505070.description: Co-stars and fellow comics discuss the witty Chicago native, who shined as a stand-up, television actor, movie star, husband, and father.

519105.title: Before They Were Kings (Vol. 1)
519105.description: Step into a comedy time machine back to the 1980’s small club circuit where the earliest standup routines of today’s legends were first performed.

520482.title: Lavell Crawford: Home for the Holidays
520482.description: Lavell Crawford’s Showtime comedy set includes funny tales of roaches eating Christmas garland, family trips to Disneyworld, and growing up chunky.

520881.title: Chris Porter: A Man From Kansas
520881.description: Kansas-based comedian Chris Porter’s comedy set about men’s very limited emotions, people who think the Earth is flat, and hipsters ruining food.

520941.title: Dominique Witten: Stop Me When I'm Lying!
520941.description: The stand up comic, actress, and “Chappelle's Show" performer gives her signature hot takes regarding the life and times of a modern comedian.

522158.title: Deon Cole - Live Comedy From the Laff House
522158.description: Stand-up comedian Deon Cole performs at the Laff House in Philadelphia, in a set taped before he became a star.

526303.title: Josh Blue: 7 More Days in the Tank
526303.description: The winner of NBC's “Last Comic Standing” stops by Denver, Colorado’s Gothic Theatre to give his takes on living with cerebral palsy.

530119.title: Chris Porter: Screaming From the Cosmos
530119.description: Known as the third place winner of NBC's Last Comic Standing, Chris Porter brings his stoner persona to this live show at the Kansas City Improv.

531374.title: Liquor House Comedy Presents Brown Sugar Night
531374.description: Welcome to Raleigh, North Carolina’s finest comedy club, where three hilarious women of color bring their A-game material to the stage.

535643.title: Alonzo Bodden: Who's Paying Attention
535643.description: “Last Comic Standing” winner Alonzo Bodden jokes about outlandish pop culture, as well as spoofing well-known stereotypes, in this live special.

535647.title: Andrew Dice Clay: One Night With Dice
535647.description: A rare stand-up set and Q&A session with Andrew Dice Clay, performed at a Philly comedy club before he hit it big on the comedy and TV circuit.

535651.title: Eddie Griffin: Undeniable
535651.description: Eddie Griffin brings his blunt and undeniable style to this stand-up set about athletes and racial stereotypes, relationships, and human mistakes.

535653.title: Jeff Dunham: All Over the Map
535653.description: A comedy set and travelogue by comedian Jeff Dunham as he and his ventriloquist’s dummies perform globally from Iceland and London to Israel.

539591.title: Tony Baker's Scaredy Cat
539591.description: Comedian Tony Baker's 2016 live show in New Mexico where he discusses his many fears, from flies in the bathroom to clowns and ghosts.

544241.title: DeMarcus Cousins Presents Boogie's Comedy Slam
544241.description: NBA All-Star DeMarcus “Boogie” Cousins teams up with host Mike Epps for this hilarious comedy special featuring Gary Owen, Karlous Miller, and more.

547565.title: Iliza Shlesinger: Freezing Hot
547565.description: The acclaimed Last Comic Standing winner explains how women hate being cold, but love cold weather, and other hilarious observations.

547566.title: Dov Davidoff: Lower Your Expectations
547566.description: Performing in Chicago, the brash stand-up comedian discusses the nonsensical truths in our culture, and wonders what America is becoming.

547568.title: John Heffron: Middle Class Funny
547568.description: The Michigan comedian discusses his deep frustrations in marriage, loathing for when people are passive-aggressive, and other relatable subjects.

547570.title: Jeff Dunham: Spark of Insanity
547570.description: Jeff and his felt friends Walter, Melvin the Superhero Guy, Peanut, and others share their latest and greatest thoughts about our times.

547576.title: Alonzo Bodden: Historically Incorrect
547576.description: The New York native and Last Comic Standing winner examines historical inaccuracies of the past, which have led to our present situation.

547579.title: Danny Bhoy: Subject to Change
547579.description: The Scottish stand-up comic dazzles a Montreal audience with his one-of-a-kind style of storytelling and self-deprecating sensibility.

547614.title: Kevin Smith: Silent but Deadly
547614.description: Filmmaker Kevin Smith is anything but quiet in this new comedy special that was recorded an hour before his widely reported massive heart attack.

551878.title: Thou Shalt Laugh, the Deuce: Tim Conway
551878.description: Funnyman Tim Conway presents a roster of America’s zaniest Christian comedians, including SNL alum, Victoria Jackson and other clean cut-ups.

551879.title: Thou Shalt Laugh 4: John Tesh
551879.description: John Tesh hosts magician Dana Daniels, Luigi the Psychic Parrot, and six Christian comedians for a rib-tickling session of clean family fun.

551973.title: Thou Shalt Laugh: Patricia Heaton
551973.description: Flat-out fun for the whole family awaits, as Emmy-winner Patricia Heaton hosts a lineup featuring seven of the funniest Christian comics around.

552679.title: T.K. Kirkland: Who Raised You?
552679.description: Underground comedy legend T.K. Kirkland paints vivid pictures with his hilarious storytelling and jokes in a new comedy special.

560088.title: Chonda Pierce: Have I Got a Story for You
560088.description: The Christian stand-up comedian nicknamed "The Queen of Clean" waxes comedic on fairy tales, differences between the genders, NASCAR, and the Bible.

560229.title: Chonda Pierce: Be Afraid... Be Very Afraid
560229.description: The funny lady looks fear in the eye and laughs, sharing her secret weapons: comedy sketches, faux commercials, stories, and heartfelt songs

560231.title: Chonda Pierce: Did I Say That Out Loud?
560231.description: The sassy comedienne dishes on Hollywood, Botox, purse puppies, and health food, weighing them against southern barbecue, tithing, and tumbling wigs.

560271.title: Chonda Pierce: I'm Kind of a Big Deal
560271.description: The comic shares hilarious stories about Middle East war zones, ministering to supermodels and cheerleaders, Hollywood, and boating with chainsaws.

560612.title: Chonda Pierce: A Piece of My Mind
560612.description: From her hometown of Murfreesboro, Tennessee,  the popular Christian comic gets down-to-earth on shopping, diets, menopause, raising kids, and more.

560955.title: Jeff Allen: Happy Wife, Happy Life
560955.description: Humorist Jeff Allen explores the hilarious highs and lows of married life and raising children in this clean and fun comedy special.

561319.title: The Big Black Comedy Show (Vol. 1)
561319.description: Oscar-winning actress/ hilarious stand up Mo'Nique co-hosts this all-star comedy show featuring some of the best comics in the business.

561320.title: The Big Black Comedy Show (Vol. 2)
561320.description: Award-winning comedian/actress Mo'Nique returns as the co-host of this hilarious special, which includes a killer lineup of comics.

561321.title: The Big Black Comedy Show (Vol. 4)
561321.description: Ralphie May hosts this laugh-a-minute comedy special, which includes hilarious comics like Jay Phillips, Tommy Chunn, Alex Thomas, and more.

561814.title: The Big Black Comedy Show (Vol. 5)
561814.description: An outrageously funny stand-up comedy special with an all-star line-up of African American entertainers, hosted by the multi-talented Michael Colyar.

562051.title: Thou Shalt Laugh 3: Sinbad
562051.description: Comedy superstar Sinbad and his roster of top Christian humorists provide funny, family-friendly entertainment, in this episode of the series.

562176.title: Chonda Pierce: This Ain't Prettyville
562176.description: The family-friendly comedian dishes on living in a small town, the perks of taxidermy, and the thrills of exploding toilets and fried bologna.

567276.title: Paul Mooney: A Piece of My Mind
567276.description: The razor-sharp verbal stylings of Paul Mooney spare no political or celebrity foolishness in this outrageously funny stand-up concert.

569452.title: Kevin Hart: Laugh at My Pain
569452.description: The hilarious comic keeps it real by showing his Philadelphia roots, where he first started honing the skills that would make him a comedy superstar.

578318.title: Laugh N' Tell: A Valentines Day Special
578318.description: Laugh n Tell is a Valentine's Day stand up comedy show hosted by the late, great Rasheed Thurmond. Other well known comedians such as Smokey, Roberto Vanderbooth, and Mike Bonner from BETS's Comic View, Razor from Bad Boys of Comedy and Drew Frazier of Russell Simmons Def Comedy Jam round off Cupid's gang of comedians.

580449.title: Rob Gordon: Problematic
580449.description: Rising comedy star Rob Gordon riffs on the perils of football, why great athletes don’t know their fathers, and learning how to trust his new son.

583763.title: Sebastian Maniscalco: Aren't You Embarrassed?
583763.description: The comedian returns home to a sold-out audience in Chicago, to burn modern-day society through the lens of his old-world Italian-American upbringing.

589846.title: Tom Wilson: Bigger Than You
589846.description: Best known for his role as Biff Tannen in the Back to the Future series, comic Tom Wilson tells some hilarious stories and plays a little guitar.

589850.title: Tammy Pescatelli's Way After School Special
589850.description: The comic tells it like it is on stage at her old high school, where the former captain of the cheerleaders shows off her witty takes on the world.

589856.title: Jeff Dunham: Unhinged in Hollywood
589856.description: The comedian and his puppets perform in the gorgeous Dolby Theatre, featuring hilarious sketches with surprise guests and lots of laughs.

589870.title: Dan Cummins: Get Outta Here, Devil!
589870.description: The podcaster shares outrageous stories of his sexual experience with a banana peel, his dislike of strangers, and how to fix the world.

609256.title: #IMomSoHard Live
609256.description: A two-woman show about friendship, periods, sex after marriage, body image, and parenting failures from comics Kristin Hensley and Jen Smedley.

609382.title: Alonzo Bodden: Heavy Lightweight
609382.description: Last Comic Standing winner Alonzo Bodden straddles the line between deep and droll with hilarious commentary on Kanye, Alexa, and our absurd reality.

609523.title: Melinda Hill: Inappropriate
609523.description: Comedian Melinda Hill shares hilarious and searingly honest truths through physical comedy, confessions, and jokes on timely topics.

609562.title: Lavell Crawford: New Look, Same Funny
609562.description: Comedian and “Breaking Bad” icon Lavell Crawford shows off his new weight loss, new attitude, and explains how to cope with the mean streets.

610599.title: Lewis Black: Thanks for Risking Your Life
610599.description: Filmed in the midst of his tour and on the last night before America’s national lockdown due to COVID-19, Lewis Black delivers a searing comedy set.

613737.title: Jim Gaffigan: Quality Time
613737.description: The comedian discusses why we aren’t honest about not wanting to attend events, lying to children, and so much more in this hilarious special.

613858.title: Musical Comedy Whore!
613858.description: Actor David Pevsner tells all in a one-man musical comedy performance that chronicles his personal journey from shame to self-acceptance.

619871.title: Comedy Hustle
619871.description: In this uncensored and untamed comedy special, comedy icons Tyler Craig, Big Rome, Karl "Special K" Douglas, and Dekeys keep it real, rough, and funny.

619878.title: Rodney Perry : Nothing but the Truth
619878.description: The high energy stand-up rises to comedy greatness, performing  in Birmingham, Alabama, examining life’s highs and lows, love, happiness, and more.

620912.title: Craig Ferguson: Just Being Honest
620912.description: This Grammy-nominated special has the comedian discussing deeply profound and stupid everyday things like shoes that resemble feet.

621247.title: Laffapalooza (Vol. 6)
621247.description: Laugh along with the freshest, funniest stand up comedians on the scene, including Geoff Brown, Speedy, Benji Brown, and Gerald Kelly.

625330.title: Zoltan Kaszas: Cat Jokes
625330.description: Born in Budapest, Hungary and raised in San Diego, California, this comic first stepped onstage at the age of 19 and was hooked immediately.

628005.title: Mike Goodwin: Whatchanotgonedo Is Just Laugh at These Jokes!
628005.description: Enjoy the warm comic stylings of this southern gentleman with a curious mind, love for people, and heart for God, who is in a class all his own.

630872.title: Gary Owen: #DoinWhatIDo
630872.description: The so-called “Funniest Serviceman in America” draws from his multiracial experience to lambast culture wars on social media and in his own home.

633037.title: Leanne Morgan: So Yummy
633037.description: The stand up comic discusses dogs, cheerleading camp, the struggles of being an empty nester, and joining Weight Watchers for the 7th time.

633054.title: Harmony McElligott: The Struggle Continues
633054.description: In his first one hour stand-up comedy special, the comic discusses his unusual name, his thoughts on “127 Hours,” and buying off-brand soap.

633055.title: Tiffany Haddish: She Ready! From the Hood to Hollywood!
633055.description: The sensational “Girls Trip” star shares about her positive outlook on life, growing up in the foster care system, and working with legends.

636013.title: Craig Shoemaker-the Lovemaster...Unzipped
636013.description: Stand-up comedian, writer, and actor Craig Shoemaker returns, in the guise of his alter-ego, "The Lovemaster," and wows a live audience of fans.

639194.title: Hilarious
639194.description: In interviews with writers, actors, and stand-up comedians director Marc Brissett teases out some of the best material in the history of comedy.

639207.title: The Marvelous Mrs Shenkman
639207.description: This part-comedy special, part-puppet show tracks the identity crisis of a speed-talking comedian who suddenly finds herself pregnant at the age of 40.

643673.title: Russell Peters: Deported
643673.description: The hilarious Russell Peters performs at a stadium in Mumbai where he laments gaining weight, spoofs Bollywood vocals, and talks about being a dad.

643675.title: Preacher Lawson: Get to Know Me
643675.description: The comedian and “America’s Got Talent” finalist spills all about incontinence in his pants, sleeping in a race-car bed as a teen, and being vegan.

643873.title: Heather McDonald: I Don't Mean to Brag
643873.description: The smart, edgy, sometimes-shocking comic holds nothing back, especially when recounting the hilarious ways she attempts to balance fame and family.

643902.title: Eddie Izzard: Definite Article
643902.description: This hilarious special captures the stand-up performing in the Shaftesbury Theatre in London, during the comic’s legendary 12 week run.

643952.title: Eddie Izzard: Dress to Kill
643952.description: Britain’s Eddie Izzard took the U.S. by storm with this double Emmy-winning comedy set in San Francisco where she takes on a world of sly topics.

646380.title: Eddie Griffin: E-Niggma
646380.description: Comedian Eddie Griffin slays in this Showtime standup special celebrating the 10th anniversary of his Sahara Hotel and Casino residency in Las Vegas.

649560.title: Clean Cut: Sunday's Best Comedy
649560.description: Laugh along with Christian comedians as they share their perspectives on different pastors’ styles, their own temptations, and ushers.

654770.title: Gina Brillon: The Floor Is Lava
654770.description: The stand up comic discusses her childhood, the secrets that men have learned about dating apps, and life with her Midwestern husband.

655687.title: Mike Cannon: Life Begins
655687.description: The new father discusses how his friends don’t really understand his work as a stand up comedian, his take on abortion, and road rage.

659419.title: Bob Smiley: Tartar Terrorist
659419.description: The clean comedian discusses his experiences in Arkansas, why he won’t make fun of the Clintons, and his weird moments at the airport.

659505.title: Dennis Regan: Dennisland
659505.description: The King Of Queens writer comes out swinging hard with his quick wit and flawless delivery in this stand-up special. Presented by Dry Bar Comedy.

659619.title: Drew Barth: Shoulda Tried Harder
659619.description: Born outside of Seattle, what started as a high school dare has led to Drew Barth’s rise as one of the fastest growing comedy stars in the Northwest.

659621.title: Eric O'Shea: Life: It's Not Your Fault!
659621.description: A 25-year veteran of stand-up comedy, Eric O'Shea has performed with Betty White at the Creative Emmy Awards and has appeared on America's Got Talent.

659623.title: Greg Warren: Fish Sandwich
659623.description: This nationally touring headliner has performed on Late Night with Seth Meyers, Last Comic Standing, Comedy Central Presents, BET, CMT and more.

659626.title: Dwight Slade: Animal Cracker
659626.description: Winner of 2017’s Boston Comedy Festival, Dwight Slade combines a raging voice of justice with the snickering attitude of a high school prankster.

659665.title: Josh Sneed: Live in the Dessert
659665.description: Hailing from the great city of Cincinnati, Josh Sneed comes to Dry Bar bringing “new life” to comedy. Being funny 24/7 is hard, but he pulls it off.

660148.title: Warren B. Hall: Mostly Kid Stuff
660148.description: Simply put, Warren B. Hall is not what you're expecting. He purposely avoids using the white vs. black angle done by many mainstream black comedians.

666036.title: Bill Engvall: Just Sell Him for Parts
666036.description: The multi-platinum recording artist performs his 2015 stand-up special before a live audiance at Rockford Illinois’ Coronado Performing Arts Center.

666037.title: Blue Collar Comedy Tour Rides Again
666037.description: Bill Engvall, Ron “Tater Salad” White, Jeff Foxworthy and Larry the Cable Guy return for their redneck laughs and trademark spins on everyday life.

666039.title: Blue Collar Comedy Tour: One for the Road
666039.description: The unapologetically unrefined foursome returned to the stage in 2005 to wax redneck before a live audience at the Warner Theatre in Washington, D.C.

673994.title: Ralphie May: Prime Cut
673994.description: Ralphie May returns with another installment of his hilarious insights and observations filmed at The Tennessee Theatre in Knoxville, TN.

676163.title: John Moyer: Welcome to My World
676163.description: With twenty years of stand-up comedy experience, a natural quick-wit, and improvisational showmanship, John Moyer connects with every audience.

676172.title: Ricky Glore: Dad Bod
676172.description: Stand-up comedian and comedy writer Ricky Glore brings his high energy and confidence to the Dry Bar stage.

677757.title: Rachel Bradley: Alpha Chick
677757.description: Rachel Bradley takes prisoners in her first standup comedy special release, filmed live at the El Portal Theatre in North Hollywood.

678123.title: Shang is... Shangry!
678123.description: Taped in front of a packed New York house, the in-your-face comic dishes on race, religion, drug legalization and what really makes him so ‘shangry.’

678197.title: Ben Bailey: Road Rage
678197.description: Following Ben Bailey's successful run as the original host of Bravo’s Ca$h Cab came the genial driver’s hilarious debut stand-up comedy special.

680256.title: Kevin Hart: Let Me Explain
680256.description: A documentary following Kevin Hart's 2012 international standup comedy tour, which included performances in 80 cities around the globe.

682997.title: Steve Treviño: Relatable
682997.description: America's most relatable spouse offers a gut-busting glimpse into married life in this stand-up special recorded live in Corpus Christi, Texas.

683389.title: Ralphie May: Girth of a Nation
683389.description: The predecessor to the highly rated Prime Cut, this special finds the ebonics-fluent comic getting comfortable in equal-opportunity offender mode.

688741.title: Jeff Jena: Old Dog, New Jokes
688741.description: Jeff Jena, one of the top corporate and cruise comics, has 33 years of live performance experience, giving him the ability to work for any audience.

688749.title: John Deming: Sadder Than Most Horses
688749.description: One of the most exciting and young comedians from Utah, John Deming’s performances are as unpredictable as they are side-splitting.

688788.title: Jeff Wayne: Big Daddy Kicks It!
688788.description: Dubbed "Big Daddy" by Billy Crystal and Robin Williams on an HBO Comic Relief show, Jeff Wayne has been part of the stand-up comedy scene for years.

688791.title: Andy Forrester: Most of This is Baby Fat
688791.description: Andy Forrester's brand of off-the-wall humor has made him a fan favorite at comedy clubs all over the country for nearly two decades.

688850.title: Josh Novey: Tickling Grizzlies
688850.description: Starting his stand-up career after returning from the Iraq War, this clean comic uses his humor and easy-going stage presence to entertain thousands.

700898.title: Matt Falk: Unlit
700898.description: Dry Bar Comedy, Utah’s only family-friendly stand-up club, welcomes the “effortlessly funny” Canadian touring comic and festival performer.

700913.title: Robert Mac: Know More
700913.description: Dry Bar Comedy, Utah’s only family-friendly stand-up comedy club, welcomes this not-too-smart, not-too-subtle but embracingly silly comedian.

701251.title: Steve Bruner: Simply Put
701251.description: Dry Bar Comedy, Utah’s only family-friendly stand-up club, welcomes to the stage a perfectly normal looking-guy—until he opens his mouth.

702193.title: Bill Bellamy: I Want My Life Back
702193.description: Live from Tribeca, the comic delves into the complexities of life while appreciating the simple things in this new era of quarantines and mandates.

702195.title: Josh Gondelman: People Pleaser
702195.description: The comic who just wants everyone to have a good time explores the pressures of appearing in his friends’ dreams and choosing the right wedding DJ.

702199.title: Mike Speenberg: Uphill Both Ways
702199.description: Dry Bar Comedy, Utah’s only family-friendly stand-up club, welcomes to the stage this 20-year veteran as a professionally touring stand-up comedian.

704688.title: Blue Collar Comedy Tour: The Movie
704688.description: Get four helpings of down-home, country-fried comedy while touring America with Jeff Foxworthy, Bill Engvall, Larry the Cable Guy, and Ron White.

708596.title: Frenchy: Turn It Up!
708596.description: Frenchy is back with his most outrageous special yet! This unforgettable show is full of wild banter, ridiculous stories, and unbeatable crowd work.

725373.title: Danny Cho: Liquor Store Baby
725373.description: The former regular on MadTV and Parks and Recreation releases his debut one-hour stand-up special about growing up in the family booze business.

100000283.title: Anjelah Johnson: Mahalo & Goodnight
100000283.description: In her fourth stand-up comedy special, Anjelah Johnson dishes on awkward massages, home invasions, spiders, and being a full-grown child.

100001074.title: Brian Bates: Uber Important
100001074.description: Brian Bates spent 20 years in corporate America before launching a stand-up comedy career. Now he brings his unique perspective to the Dry Bar stage.

100001164.title: Andre Ferrell: Rude Awakening

100001440.title: Drew Lynch: Concussed
100001440.description: In Drew's first-ever special, nothing is off limits: COVID, cops, Jesus, gender, drinking, depression and other topics he's unqualified to talk about.

100002072.title: Matt Rife: Only Fans
100002072.description: Comedian Matt Rife shares his unique perspective on the world in his debut special after ten years of performing stand-up comedy.

0300005099.title: The Comedy Shop
0300005099.description: An amazing variety of legendary comedians tell jokes and laugh along with host Norm Crosby in this hilarious and light-hearted variety series.

0300008328.title: Stand Up Nashville
0300008328.description: Aspiring comics from rural America join a popular comedic host, to showcase their abilities in front of an audience at Nashville’s Zanies Comedy Club.

0300000008.title: Dry Bar Comedy
0300000008.description: This series features some of the most hilarious, originally-crafted, and cleanest stand-up comedy ever performed. Warning… this is safe for work!

02060.title: Just for Laughs Gags
02060.description: Welcome to the world-famous Just for Laughs Gags. Our PRANKS generate some of the funniest reactions, and most awkward moments ever caught on camera.
